  "text": "The Grafana datasource plugin query flow begins with the HTTP API handler QueryMetricsV2 in pkg/api/ds_query.go:68, which receives a MetricRequest from the /ds/query endpoint. This handler delegates to hs.queryDataService.QueryData (line 81), which is an instance of query.Service.\n\nThe query.Service is implemented by ServiceImpl in pkg/services/query/query.go. The QueryData method (line 126) parses the metric request into queries grouped by datasource (parseMetricRequest, line 109), and for single datasources, calls handleQuerySingleDatasource (line 120, implemented at line 288).\n\nhandleQuerySingleDatasource constructs a backend.QueryDataRequest and determines whether to use the plugin client (single-tenant flow) or query-service client (multi-tenant flow). For the single-tenant flow, it calls s.pluginClient.QueryData(ctx, req) at line 322.\n\nThe plugin client is implemented by the Service in pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go. The QueryData method (line 50) retrieves the plugin from the registry and calls p.QueryData(ctx, req) on the underlying plugin implementation.\n\nFor gRPC-based plugins, the backend plugin execution occurs in pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go. The ClientV2.QueryData method (line 162) converts the backend.QueryDataRequest to protobuf format using backend.ToProto().QueryDataRequest(req) at line 167, calls c.DataClient.QueryData at line 168 to execute the query via gRPC, and converts the response back using backend.FromProto().QueryDataResponse(protoResp) at line 189.\n\nThe response backend.QueryDataResponse contains data frames returned by the plugin. This response is sent back through the call chain to pkg/api/ds_query.go:87, where hs.toJsonStreamingResponse(c.Req.Context(), resp) serializes it for HTTP transmission.\n\nData frame serialization occurs in pkg/api/response/response.go. The JSONStreaming function (line 199) creates a StreamingResponse with the backend.QueryDataResponse. When WriteTo is called (line 153), it uses jsoniter.ConfigCompatibleWithStandardLibrary to create an encoder (line 164) and calls enc.Encode(r.body) to serialize the response to JSON (line 165).\n\nAlternatively, for the new K8s-based query service, requests route through pkg/registry/apis/query/query.go. The queryREST.Connect method (line 115) handles POST requests to the /apis/query.grafana.app/v0alpha1 endpoint. It calls handleQuery (line 244), which constructs a dtos.MetricRequest and delegates to service.QueryData. The response is wrapped as a query.QueryDataResponse and returned to responder.Object.\n\nFor the aggregator/plugin handler in pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go, the QueryDataHandler (line 20) receives requests, converts them to backend format, calls h.client.QueryData (line 75), and returns the response via responder.Object as an aggregationv0alpha1.QueryDataResponse (line 86), which wraps the backend.QueryDataResponse."
}

